President Obama has nominated Stephanie A. Finley and Claude J. Kelly III to serve on the United States District Courts. Finley has been serving as the United States Attorney for the Western District of Louisiana since 2010 and has a distinguished record of public service. Kelly has been the Chief Federal Defender in the Federal Public Defender's Office for the Eastern District of Louisiana since 2014 and has extensive experience as a criminal defense attorney. Both nominees have shown a strong commitment to justice and integrity throughout their careers.